Ad Text:
Senior Data Engineer

$200k – $230k package · Sydney or Remote (Australia)

About the Company

Join a fast-growing technology business that builds modern data and analytics platforms to power customer and market insights.
They value trust, collaboration and autonomy, with a culture that rewards impact and supports life outside of work.

About the Role

As Senior Data Engineer, you’ll design and operate the core data environment that ingests, organises and serves high-volume customer and market data.
This is a hands-on position blending data engineering and data infrastructure, focusing on R, Python and SQL and working across on-premises and cloud environments.

What You’ll Do

Design and build scalable, high-performance data pipelines to ingest and process large, complex datasets from multiple internal and external sources.

Model and manage data flows and schemas to ensure quality, consistency and reliability.

Implement best practices in data governance, access control, monitoring and observability.

Work with product and analytics teams to align data architecture with business goals.

Automate infrastructure provisioning and deployments using modern DevOps and Infrastructure-as-Code tools.

Provide production support, including continuous improvement of system performance, availability and disaster recovery.

What You Bring

Degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics or equivalent experience.

Proficiency in R, Python and SQL with strong data modelling and query optimisation skills.

Solid understanding of distributed systems, modern data storage (e.g. S3, columnar stores) and streaming technologies (e.g. Kafka).

Experience with cloud platforms (AWS, GCP) and Linux.

Familiarity with orchestration tools (Airflow, Dagster) and container technologies (Docker, Kubernetes).

Strong communication skills and the ability to work effectively in small, fast-moving teams as well as larger enterprise environments.

Nice to Have

Experience working end-to-end in small, agile environments, taking full ownership of design and delivery.

Exposure to modern data formats (Delta Lake, Apache Iceberg) and data lakehouse architectures.

Experience with observability tools (Prometheus, Grafana).

Why Join

Play a key role in shaping a greenfield data platform used for advanced analytics and data-driven decision making.

Work with modern tooling across both cloud and on-prem environments.

Join a supportive, collaborative culture with flexibility for remote work.

Software Engineer – Manufacturing Management Systems

About the Company

InTimeTec (Australia) Pty Ltd is part of a global technology services organization founded in 2009, with offices across the United States, Europe, South Korea, India, Dubai, and Australia. With over 1,000 employees worldwide, we partner with clients to deliver scalable software solutions across industries including manufacturing, retail, finance, healthcare, and government. Our culture is built on trust, transparency, and long-term relationships—helping businesses succeed while fostering a meaningful workplace for our people.

About the Role

This is a full-time hybrid role for a Software Engineer - Manufacturing Management System located in Greater Melbourne Area, with some work-from-home flexibility. The Software Engineer will be responsible for developing, testing, and maintaining software systems for manufacturing management. Day-to-day tasks include coding, debugging, and optimizing software solutions, collaborating with cross-functional teams to understand and implement requirements, and ensuring the effective performance of the manufacturing management system.

Key Responsibilities

Develop, test, and optimize MMS features, tools, and processes.

Build and maintain web applications using .NET and ColdFusion.

Write clean, scalable, and maintainable code.

Troubleshoot and resolve software issues promptly.

Participate in requirements gathering, design, development, testing, and deployment.

Analyze user/business needs and implement system enhancements.

Stay current with industry technologies and best practices.

Support ERP (JDE/others) integration and web services.

Skills & Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, IT, or related field.

Minimum 3+ years of ColdFusion experience.

Strong UI development skills: jQuery, Bootstrap, HTML, CSS, JavaScript.

Proficiency in:

.NET, RESTful APIs, Git, Azure DevOps

MS SQL Server, Entity Framework, SSIS

Spring MVC, Spring Boot, Microservices, ASP.NET, Razor Pages

Experience with ERP systems (JDE preferred).

Strong troubleshooting, problem-solving, and independent working skills.

What We Offer

Opportunity to work on impactful, enterprise-level applications.

Exposure to a wide technology stack and modern development practices.

Collaborative and supportive team environment.

A culture built on trust, transparency, and long-term growth.

Location

Greater Melbourne Area (South Eastern Suburbs) - Onsite / Hybrid

Job Type: Full-time

Work Authorisation:

Australia (Preferred)

Application Deadline: 24/10/2025

Ad Text:
About ACMI

ACMI is your museum of screen culture. Watch, play, make and discover the universe of screen-based art, films, TV and videogames. Visit us in Naarm/Melbourne's Fed Square, online and on tour. Our museum attracts millions of visitors through a vibrant offer of exhibitions, screenings, commissions and festivals. ACMI's industry, education and creative incubator programs inspire and develop the next generation of screen creatives. We are a globally recognised hub that connects people, communities, technology and ideas to shape our futures. More at acmi.net.au

About the role

ACMI is seeking a Platform Reliability Engineer to manage reliability, security, and scalability of the ACMI's ICT infrastructure across on-premise and cloud environments. The role plays a critical part in maintaining high availability of services, implementing robust disaster recovery strategies, and proactively identifying and resolving system issues. This is a new full-time ongoing role reporting to the Head of Systems & Infrastructure.

What you'll bring to the role

Relevant qualifications and practical experience working with: Cisco networking products and protocols, cloud services Azure and AWS supporting networking and compute and Logic Monitor or similar. Strong working knowledge of LANs, SANs, Azure, AWS, VMware, ICT security systems, wireless networks, firewalls, routers, core switches, and server/network monitoring tools.
Extensive hands-on experience managing ICT infrastructure across on-premises and cloud environments, with strong technical expertise in Windows, Linux, and macOS systems.
Strong knowledge of network and system security practices, including experience with anti-virus, spam prevention, and endpoint protection tools.
Experience designing and implementing disaster recovery and business continuity strategies.
Highly developed conceptual and analytical skills applicable to successful technical troubleshooting, problem solving across a range of technical/ systems applications/issues and ability to evaluate and implement continual improvements to ICT support systems.

What we offer

Full-time ongoing Grade 4.1 role, with a starting salary of $97,955 plus super.
A talented, committed and creative team of people with a passion for screen culture, technology and media, cultural diversity, and inspiring new forms of creativity in our communities. A museum and workspace that provides an exceptional space to collaborate with colleagues located in the heart of Melbourne in Federation Square (just a 5 min walk from Flinders Street station).
As a valued team member, you can enjoy complimentary and discounted tickets, discounts at our shop and cafe, access to wellbeing activities, learning and development programs and our Employee Assistance Program. Flexible working, including a mix of onsite and work from home days depending on your role. Visit the ACMI website to learn more about working with us.

How to apply

To obtain a position description and apply online visit ACMI Careers. Follow the online application process, submit your resume and a one-page cover letter explaining why you're interested in the role and how your experience makes you a good fit. Please contact us via peopleandculture@acmi.net.au or 03 8663 2200 to discuss making adjustments to the recruitment process for your accessibility needs.

Applications close Sunday 5 October 2025 at 11:59pm.

Please note interviews will be held on Tuesday 14 October 2025.

ACMI is a child safe workplace and actively promotes the safety, wellbeing and inclusion of all children from all backgrounds. ACMI is an equal opportunity employer, committed to building an inclusive workplace that supports diverse thinking and innovation. We encourage applications from First Nations People, people of culturally diverse backgrounds, Deaf and Disabled people and people from the LGBTIQA+ community. All sectors of the community are welcome to apply.

Applicants must be an Australian Citizen, Permanent Resident or hold a valid work permit or visa. Work eligibility will be checked as part of the recruitment process. The successful applicant is required to complete reference and background checks prior to employment, including a Working with Children Check where required and National Police Check.

*Naarm is the traditional Aboriginal name for Melbourne which encompasses the traditional lands of the Kulin Nation, a collective of five Aboriginal language groups, the Wurundjeri, Boon Wurrung, Wathaurrung, Taungurung and Dja Dja Wurrung.

Build the Platform That Changes Business Forever

Two Dot AI | Full-Stack AI Engineer | $125-150k AUD

The Opportunity

We're building the deployment and management platform for autonomous AI agents for business. Not chatbots. Actual agents that run entire business workflows.

We have the clients. We have the use cases. We have the blueprint. Join us while we build the infrastructure that makes it real.

You'll join the team that is building the platform that deploys and manages an agentic workforce - starting with our own clients, then expanding globally to transform how businesses work.

Who We're After

Looking for someone who wants to embrace AI-vibe coding — moving fast, iterating, and working in a way that avoids too much spaget.

You'll:

Ship, build, test and deploy AI Agents.

Help shape the platform as it comes online (devops experience would be really nice).

Optionally dip into client-facing work ("Forward Deployed Engineer"), but not required.

Jack of all trades: UI / Backend / Databases / Infra Devops / Saftey Testing / Cloud / Mentoring Interns

The Technical Challenge

You'll work with:

AI Coding Tools: Claude Code, Codex, Gemini CLI, Open Router, Warp and many others.

Google Cloud AI Stack: Vertex AI Agent Builder, Extensions, Search & Conversation

MCP Servers: Build and host Model Context Protocol servers for business integrations

Multi-cloud Architecture: Start with GCP, extend to Azure/AWS for enterprise clients

Event-driven Systems: Real-time streaming, pub/sub, agent orchestration

Agent Infrastructure: Memory management, context handling, monitoring, self-healing

We don't expect you to know all of the above AI tools - they're too new. We need someone with the foundational skills to master them quickly.

Core Requirements

Must-haves:

2+ years shipping production code (or exceptional ability proven otherwise)

Strong Google Cloud Platform experience or simliar in Azure/AWS

Proven distributed systems and API design skills

Experience with event-driven architectures and streaming systems

Daily AI coding tool user (Claude Code, Cursor, Copilot)

Exceptional async communication

Must have existing Australian work authorisation

Standout signals:

Built platforms that scale (not just apps)

Comfortable learning bleeding-edge tech from docs and experiments

Experience with auth patterns, API gateways, observability

Can architect systems from concept to production

History of 10x productivity gains using AI tools

How We Build

AI-accelerated everything: If you're not using AI to code at 10x speed, you're already behind

Ship fast, learn faster: These tools are evolving weekly - we build, test, iterate

Own your decisions: No committees - you architect it, you build it, you own it

Customer-driven: Every feature ships to a real business within days

Who You'll Work With

Our exceptional team and you'll work directly with the founder, a proven entrepreneur who's built and exited companies before. No layers, no politics - direct access to leadership and immediate impact on company direction. This isn't his first rodeo, and he knows how to build both products and teams.

The Package

Cash: $125,000 - $150,000 AUD

Growth:

Direct path to senior positions in this expanding role

10-20% time for R&D/experimentation with new AI tools

All cloud and AI certifications covered

Daily collaboration with proven technical leadership

Reality check: This is intense, focused building. We ship when it's ready, not on arbitrary timelines. If you want predictable 9-5, this isn't it. If you want to build tools that fundamentally change how businesses operate, you've found your place.

Why Two Dot AI?

Cutting edge: Using tools that most developers haven't heard of yet

Real impact: Our agents are already saving clients 30% of their time

Funded & focused: Seed closed, products delivered, clear vision, paying customers

Small & fast: No bureaucracy, no meetings about meetings

How to Apply:

You must follow the below instructions to be considered:

Email your CV in pdf format only to careers@twodot.ai

DO NOT attach ANY other documents to the email

Write your cover letter/introduction in the BODY of the email only (do not attach a seperate document/s)

We will NOT accept ANY applications that cannot follow the above instructions.

We will not be reviewing applications made directly or only through SEEK.

Apply If:

✓ You're excited by tech so new the docs are still being written
✓ You see AI agents as the biggest opportunity in software
✓ You want to build platforms, not just features
✓ You're ready to work harder than ever on something you own

Don't Apply If:

✗ You need work-life balance
✗ You prefer established tech stacks
✗ You code without AI assistance
✗ You're looking for a safe, predictable role

About Synechron:

At Synechron, we believe in the power of digital to transform businesses for the better. Our global consulting firm combines creativity and innovative technology to deliver industry-leading digital solutions. Synechron’s progressive technologies and optimization strategies span end-to-end Artificial Intelligence, Consulting, Digital, Cloud & DevOps, Data, and Software Engineering, servicing an array of noteworthy financial services and technology firms. Through research and development initiatives in our FinLabs we develop solutions for modernization, from Artificial Intelligence and Blockchain to Data Science models, Digital Underwriting, mobile-first applications and more. Over the last 20+ years, our company has been honored with multiple employer awards, recognizing our commitment to our talented teams. With top clients to boast about, Synechron has a global workforce of 14,000+, and has 55 offices in 20 countries within key global markets.

As a Senior Software Engineer, you will play a pivotal role in the team, working within a cross-functional squad responsible for the technical design, development, and rollout of customer experiences. We are looking for someone to join our team who is passionate about creating transformative digital experiences who thrives in a collaborative environment and is constantly pushing the boundaries to help deliver outcomes that define future industry trends.

We’re interested in hearing from people who:

· Pride themselves in their ability to design, develop, and maintain software applications using Java, Springboot, AWS technologies.

· Are knowledgeable in Implementing API development and integration , ensuring seamless data flow and system interaction.

· Are constantly collaborating with cross-functional teams to define, design, and ship new features.

· Are comfortable in working with DevSecOps teams.

· Are comfortable working closely with product management to ensure alignment with business requirements and objectives.

· Can troubleshoot, debug, and upgrade existing systems, ensuring optimal performance and reliability.

· Implement robust security measures, data protection strategies, and fail-safe redundancy features.

Tech Stack:

We use a broad range of tools, languages, and frameworks. 

Strong experience in Java, Spring Boot, and RESTful API development.
Working Experience with AWS services(e.g. S3, ECS, Lambda) and observability tools like Cloudwatch, Prometheus, or Grafana.
Experience with CI/CD tools such as GitHub, GitHub Actions, ArgoCD, and automated deployment pipelines.
Exposure to AI/ML technologies, with the ability to integrate or leverage AI models to enhance data processing, automation, or system intelligence
Good experience in messaging technologies (MQ, Kafka)
Experience in Python, SQL
Experience using DevSecOps methodologies and best practice to automate deployments and testing
